thread.title: Nearly 100 false killer whales stranded off Southwest Florida
thread.title_full: Nearly 100 false killer whales stranded off Southwest Florida - Orlando Sentinel

author: orlandosentinel.com
title: Nearly 100 false killer whales stranded off Southwest Florida
text:
Nearly 100 rare false killer whales have stranded themselves off the remote coast of Southwest Florida in Everglades National Park, the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration reported Monday.
So far, 81 dead whales have been counted. One was found alive and officials continue to search for another 13.
Go to Herald.com  for the complete report.
